        <div class="large-12 medium-12 columns">
          <h2>Getting Started</h2>
          <h4 class="subheader">Downloading microscheme and its pre-requisites&hellip;</h4>

          <h5>Microscheme Compiler</h5>
          <p>The microscheme compiler is written in pure C (99), and relies only on standard C libraries. Linux and MS Windows binaries are provided. The current version is <strong>v0.6</strong></p>

            <div class="row">
              <div class="large-4 columns">
                <div class="panel callout">
                  <h5>Linux Binaries</h5>
                  <p style="font-size: 0.9em">A .tar.gz archive containing the compiler, libraries, example program, and a makefile for automating the build process</p>
                  <p style="text-align: center;"><a href="/binaries/microscheme_0.6_linux_32.tar.gz" class="button tiny" style="color: #FFFFFF; margin-bottom: 0px;">32-bit Linux</a>
                    <a href="/binaries/microscheme_0.6_linux_64.tar.gz" class="button tiny" style="color: #FFFFFF; margin-bottom: 0px;">64-bit Linux</a></p>
                </div>
              </div>

