          <hr />

          <h5>Required tools</h5>
          <p>Microscheme compiles your programs, but it does not assemble link, or upload them. These functions are provided by avr-gcc and avrdude, which are available in mainstream Linux repositories. For example:</p>
		<p>On Arch Linux, run:
<pre style="margin-top:-12px;"><code>    $ sudo pacman -S avr-gcc
    $ sudo pacman -S avrdude</code></pre></p>

		<p>On Ubuntu, run:

<pre style="margin-top:-12px;"><code>    $ sudo apt-get install gcc-avr
    $ sudo apt-get install avrdude</code></pre></p>
		<p>The <a href="http://winavr.sourceforge.net/">winavr</a> project provides a port of both these tools for MS Windows.</p>


